definition: strong/powerful/better/slightly more than/vigorous/violent/best in their category, e.g. see 百強|百强[bai3 qiang2]
to force/to compel/to strive/to make an effort

sentences.english: It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in princes.
sentences.chinese: 投靠耶和华，强似倚赖王子。

sentences.english: A bad compromise is better than a good suit.
sentences.chinese: 吃亏的和解强似胜利的诉讼。

sentences.english: The autumn harvest this year is better than that of last year.
Be superior in the temple of God temple remained hesitant hesitate.
sentences.chinese: 强似在神寺圣殿里踟躇徘徊。

sentences.english: Our great strength, like that of the dinosaur, will become incapable of proper control.
sentences.chinese: 我们的力量将强似恐龙，无从驾驭。

sentences.english: It is better to trust in the LORD than to put confidence in princes.
sentences.chinese: 投靠耶和华，强似倚赖王子。

sentences.english: It is better to take refuge in the Lord than to trust in man.
sentences.chinese: 投靠耶和华，强似倚赖人。

definition: to deceive and swindle across the board (idiom)
to be unable to bear or support
to be called/to be referred to as
to have no alternative/to be helpless
